excerpt: Storied seaside destination showcasing a range of shops & cafes, plus an amusement park & aquarium.
detail_description: Santa Monica Pier is a must-visit destination in Los Angeles, offering a variety of shops, cafes, an amusement park, and an aquarium. While there's a fee for the famous Ferris wheel and other attractions at Pacific Park, simply strolling along the pier is free and highly recommended. It's an iconic spot that shouldn't be missed, especially since it's close to downtown Santa Monica and Venice Beach Boardwalk.
name: Santa Monica Pier
address: 200 Santa Monica Pier, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Maintained by the city, this beach is fringed by a range of businesses & offers many activities.
detail_description: Santa Monica State Beach, maintained by the city, is a popular destination offering a range of activities and businesses. The 3.5-mile stretch is divided into North and South of the Pier for easy navigation. Families can enjoy mild surf, lifeguard stations, and ample restrooms. Additionally, paved pathways are perfect for walking, cycling, and rollerblading.
name: Santa Monica State Beach
address: California, USA

excerpt: Public park boasting modern architectural features plus play equipment, a splash pad & benches.
detail_description: Tongva Park, located in Santa Monica, is a 6.2-acre public park named after the indigenous Tongva people. It features modern architectural elements, play equipment, a splash pad, benches, an amphitheater, playground, garden, fountains and picnic areas. The park offers sweeping views of the Pacific Ocean and the Santa Monica Pier from its overlook. Once a parking garage turned into a lush oasis with jungle gyms and walking paths by the Pacific Ocean.
name: Tongva Park
address: 1615 Ocean Ave, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Beach house with historic home, swimming pool, fitness classes, gym, cafe & beach equipment rentals.
detail_description: Annenberg Community Beach House in Santa Monica offers a historic beachside experience with a range of amenities. The site features a swimming pool, fitness classes, gym, cafe, and beach equipment rentals. It was built on the grounds of a 1920s mansion and still retains the original marble swimming pool from that era. Additionally, it provides yoga classes, volleyball and tennis courts, and kid-friendly facilities during the summer months.
name: Annenberg Community Beach House
address: 415 Pacific Coast Hwy, Santa Monica, CA 90402, USA

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant downtown area of Santa Monica, the Farmers Market is a delightful event that takes place every Wednesday and Saturday. This bustling market transforms Third Street Promenade into a haven for food lovers, showcasing an impressive selection of organically grown fruits and vegetables, grass-fed meats, artisanal cheeses, and much more from over 85 local farms. It's not just about shopping; it's an experience where you can mingle with chefs who frequent the market to source fresh ingredients for their culinary creations.
name: Farmers Market - Wednesday/Saturday Downtown Santa Monica
address: 155-199 Arizona Ave, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Santa Monica is a coastal city west of downtown Los Angeles. Santa Monica Beach is fringed by Palisades Park, with views over the Pacific Ocean. Santa Monica Pier is home to the Pacific Park amusement park, historic Looff Hippodrome Carousel and Santa Monica Pier Aquarium. Next to the pier is Muscle Beach, an outdoor gym established in the 1930s. In the city center, Bergamot Station houses several art galleries.
detail_description: Santa Monica is a picturesque coastal city located just west of downtown Los Angeles. The city boasts the famous Santa Monica Beach, which is bordered by Palisades Park offering stunning views of the Pacific Ocean. Visitors can enjoy attractions such as the Santa Monica Pier with its Pacific Park amusement park and historic Looff Hippodrome Carousel, as well as the Muscle Beach outdoor gym. Additionally, art enthusiasts can explore numerous galleries at Bergamot Station in the city center.
name: Santa Monica
address: California, USA

excerpt: Diverse space featuring several art galleries with rotating exhibits, plus spaces for rent.
detail_description: Bergamot Station Arts Center is a must-visit destination for art enthusiasts in Santa Monica. Housed in a former industrial complex, this vibrant hub features numerous contemporary art galleries and studios showcasing diverse artworks such as paintings, sculptures, photography, and mixed media installations. The ever-evolving exhibitions and immersive events offer visitors an opportunity to immerse themselves in the rich tapestry of artistic expression that defines Southern California's cultural landscape.
name: Bergamot Station Arts Center
address: 2525 Michigan Ave, Santa Monica, CA 90404, USA

excerpt: Contemporary open-air mall since 1980 with luxury-brand shops, plus a food court & a movie theater.
detail_description: Santa Monica Place is a vibrant open-air shopping destination that has been captivating visitors since its transformation in 2010. Nestled just two blocks from the stunning Santa Monica Beach, this contemporary mall offers an impressive array of luxury-brand shops, including renowned names like Bloomingdale's and Nordstrom, alongside chic boutiques such as Hugo Boss and Tiffany & Co. The top floor boasts a delightful dining scene where you can savor crafted cocktails or fine California wines while soaking in breathtaking ocean views.
name: Santa Monica Place
address: 395 Santa Monica Pl, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

detail_description: Montana Ave is a charming and upscale shopping district located in Santa Monica, California. It's known for its trendy boutiques, stylish cafes, and unique art galleries. The avenue offers a relaxed and inviting atmosphere, perfect for leisurely strolls and people-watching. Visitors can explore a variety of high-end fashion stores, beauty salons, and specialty shops along the tree-lined street.
name: Montana Ave
address: California, USA

excerpt: Beach workout area, dating to the 1930s, with popular public bars, rings & ropes over the sand.
detail_description: Original Muscle Beach Santa Monica, established in the 1930s, is a beach workout area with public bars, rings, and ropes over the sand. It's a popular spot for both fitness enthusiasts and spectators. Located south of the pier, it offers a unique experience with acrobatic feats and muscle flexing. The beach also features retro gym equipment from the 1930s and is distinct from Muscle Beach in Venice Beach.
name: Original Muscle Beach Santa Monica
address: Ocean Front Walk, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

detail_description: Promenade Street, also known as the Third Street Promenade, is a vibrant pedestrian street located on the West Coast. It's a car-free zone where you can take a leisurely stroll and even bring your pets along. The area is bustling with an array of shopping and dining options, making it perfect for people-watching and enjoying talented street performers.
name: Promenade Street
address: 1415 3rd Street Promenade, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Education-oriented marine center with over 100 local species & hands-on exhibits like touch tanks.
detail_description: The Heal the Bay Aquarium, formerly known as the Santa Monica Pier Aquarium, is a captivating marine center located beneath the iconic Santa Monica Pier. It showcases over 100 local species of marine animals and offers interactive exhibits such as touch tanks for visitors to engage with. Operated by the esteemed nonprofit organization Heal the Bay, this award-winning aquarium aims to educate and entertain visitors of all ages about the fascinating underwater world and promote community-led efforts in protecting Santa Monica Bay.
name: Heal the Bay Aquarium
address: 1600 Ocean Front Walk, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Museum exploring Southern California's aviation history through historic aircraft & artifacts.
detail_description: The Museum of Flying, located in Southern California, is a tribute to the region's rich aviation history. Founded by Donald Douglas, Jr., the museum showcases historic aircraft and artifacts, including exhibits related to the Douglas Aircraft Company. Visitors can explore a variety of planes, replicas, and models such as the iconic Douglas DC-3 Spirit of Santa Monica. The museum also features a FedEx airplane cockpit for unique photo opportunities.
name: Museum of Flying
address: 3100 Airport Ave, Santa Monica, CA 90405, USA

excerpt: A unique assortment of artifacts devoted to state & local history in a preserved 19th-century home.
detail_description: Nestled in a well-preserved 19th-century home in Santa Monica, the California Heritage Museum offers a diverse and multicultural experience. The museum showcases an array of exhibits featuring artworks by various artists, portraits, photographs, and artifacts that detail the rich history of Californian culture. Visitors can also attend special events where they have the opportunity to meet the artists behind the masterpieces.
name: California Heritage Museum
address: 2612 Main St, Santa Monica, CA 90405, USA

excerpt: This sizable strip of grass, palm trees & walking trails features expansive ocean views.
detail_description: Palisades Park in Santa Monica, California is a spacious linear park offering stunning ocean views and a 1.5-mile paved path perfect for leisurely strolls. The park features benches, picnic areas, petanque courts, restrooms, and the historic Santa Monica Camera Obscura. It is strategically landscaped with flora to prevent erosion into the water below.
name: Palisades Park
address: Ocean Ave, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Oceanfront park with coasters, eateries & games on the pier, including an iconic Ferris wheel.
detail_description: Pacific Park on the Santa Monica Pier is a classic seaside amusement park that offers 12 rides, including the iconic Pacific Wheel Ferris wheel and the thrilling West Coaster roller coaster. The park also features various other attractions like Shark Frenzy, Inkie's Scrambler, and traditional amusement games. It's an ideal destination for families with kids or anyone seeking nostalgic fun by the beach.
name: Pacific Park on the Santa Monica Pier
address: 380 Santa Monica Pier, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Known for its bohemian spirit, Venice is a buzzing beach town with upscale commercial and residential pockets. Free-spirited Venice Boardwalk is the site of funky shops, street performers and colorful murals. Thereâ€™s also a skate park and Muscle Beach outdoor gym. Abbot Kinney Boulevard features foodie hot spots, stylish boutiques and coffee bars. A picturesque enclave of canals is surrounded by modernist homes.
detail_description: Venice, a vibrant beach town with an unmistakable bohemian vibe, is a delightful blend of upscale living and artistic flair. The iconic Venice Boardwalk buzzes with life, showcasing quirky shops, talented street performers, and stunning murals that capture the essence of this eclectic locale. Here, you can find the famous Muscle Beach outdoor gym where fitness enthusiasts gather to showcase their strength.
name: Venice
address: Los Angeles, CA, USA

detail_description: Nestled among the opulent homes of Adelaide Drive, the Santa Monica Stairs offer a challenging workout experience in a serene residential neighborhood. Originally constructed in the 1920s for local children to reach school more quickly, these stairs now draw fitness enthusiasts seeking an intense 110ft elevation change. With around 300 concrete and wooden steps, this hidden gem has gained popularity as a fun fitness challenge.
name: Santa Monica Stairs
address: 699 Adelaide Dr, Santa Monica, CA 90402, USA

detail_description: Main St is a vibrant and trendy area located southeast of the region, known for its relaxed atmosphere and a variety of shops and dining options. The street extends towards the Venice border near Rose Avenue, offering a hip and low-key stretch that attracts visitors looking for a more laid-back experience. On the other hand, northeast of downtown lies Montana Avenue, where upscale establishments cater to those seeking a more luxurious experience.
name: Main St
address: California, USA

excerpt: Posh shopping district with a range of retailers, dining & entertainment along a stylish promenade.
detail_description: Downtown Santa Monica is a vibrant and upscale district known for its posh shopping, dining, and entertainment options. The Third Street Promenade stands out as an open-air shopping area featuring upscale retailers, gourmet cafes, bakeries, and restaurants. This pedestrian-friendly business district also hosts a popular weekly farmers market. Additionally, the recent addition of the Metro Line at 4th Street and Colorado has improved connectivity to Los Angeles.
name: Downtown Santa Monica
address: 1351 3rd Street Promenade, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: 499-seat theater at the Santa Monica College featuring drama, music, dance & family shows.
detail_description: The Eli and Edythe Broad Stage at the Santa Monica College of Performing Arts Center provides a cosy theater for locals and visitors to enjoy various types of arts performances. It is one of the largest performing arts venues in Southern California, but it only seats 500 people.
name: The Eli and Edythe Broad Stage
address: Performing Arts Center - Music Building, 1310 11th St, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Ocean Park is edged by a broad beach, popular with sunbathers, surfers, and volleyball players. Joggers and bikers use the beachside path, while parks offer playgrounds and picnicking, and vegetarian eateries line Main Street. The area is dotted with modernist apartments and Craftsman bungalows, and the California Heritage Museum, in a Victorian home, shows modern art and hosts a weekly gathering of food trucks.
detail_description: Ocean Park is a vibrant coastal neighborhood with a wide sandy beach that attracts sunbathers, surfers, and volleyball enthusiasts. The area features a beachside path for joggers and bikers, as well as parks with playgrounds and picnic areas. Main Street is lined with vegetarian restaurants, modernist apartments, and Craftsman bungalows. Additionally, the California Heritage Museum showcases modern art in a Victorian home and hosts weekly food truck gatherings.
name: Ocean Park
address: Santa Monica, CA, USA

excerpt: Counter-serve parlor offering sundaes, cones & shakes made with organic, homemade ice cream.
detail_description: Sweet Rose Creamery is a delightful ice cream parlor that offers a variety of treats such as sundaes, cones, shakes, and even ice cream cakes. As part of the Rustic Canyon Restaurant Group, it sources its ingredients from the nearby Santa Monica Farmers Market to ensure freshness and quality. The flavors range from year-round classics like fresh mint to seasonal options like Blood Orange Sorbet.
name: Sweet Rose Creamery
address: 225 26th St #51, Santa Monica, CA 90402, USA

detail_description: The Santa Monica Looff Hippodrome is a historic landmark adjacent to the Santa Monica Pier, dating back to 1916. It was built by Charles D. Looff and is now part of the National Register of Historic Places. The building houses vintage merry-go-rounds and carousels, including the iconic Looff Hippodrome Carousel with its hand-carved horses and festive band music. The whimsical arches and turrets make it a must-see attraction at the pier.
name: Santa Monica Looff Hippodrome
address: 1619 Ocean Front Walk, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Upscale-casual eatery for simply prepared seafood & a wide-ranging raw bar with views of the water.
detail_description: Blue Plate Oysterette is an upscale-casual eatery offering simply prepared seafood and a wide-ranging raw bar with views of the water. The restaurant's Santa Monica location near the popular Ocean Ave and Santa Monica Pier is a neighborhood staple where guests can enjoy fresh seafood on the outdoor patio overlooking the Pacific Ocean. The menu features lobster rolls, oysters, New England steamers, fresh fish dishes, and a great selection of beer, wine, and cocktails.
name: Blue Plate Oysterette
address: 1355 Ocean Ave, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Popular urban park includes lawn bowling, a playground & 2 tennis courts, plus a rental clubhouse.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Santa Monica, Douglas Park is a delightful urban retreat that offers a variety of activities for visitors of all ages. Spanning just one block and conveniently located near bustling Wilshire Boulevard, this park might be easy to miss at first glance. However, once you step inside its serene environment, you'll discover a beautifully manicured lawn bowling green that leads to winding paths adorned with majestic trees.
name: Douglas Park
address: 2439 Wilshire Blvd, Santa Monica, CA 90403, USA

excerpt: Iconic 3.5-mi. beach with a promenade & pier, featuring an amusement park & restaurants.
detail_description: Santa Monica Beach is a 3.5-mile iconic stretch with a lively promenade and famous pier, featuring an amusement park and various dining options. It's considered one of the best swimming beaches in Southern California, with calm waters in Santa Monica Bay. The beach offers more than just swimming, as there are shops and restaurants on the pier, along with games and rides at the amusement park.
name: Santa Monica Beach
address: Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Unique, lively mile-long thoroughfare with popular & vintage shops, restaurants & galleries.
detail_description: Abbot Kinney Boulevard is a vibrant and unique mile-long street in Venice Beach, offering an eclectic mix of popular and vintage shops, restaurants, galleries, and colorful murals. It's a hipster haven with avant-garde fashion boutiques, artisanal coffee shops, and gourmet eateries that push the boundaries of gastronomy. The area exudes creativity and innovation, making it a dynamic shopping destination unlike any other.
name: Abbot Kinney Blvd
address: Los Angeles, CA, USA

excerpt: Colorful, modern hostel 2 blocks from the beach, offering a game room, free Wi-Fi & a guest kitchen.
detail_description: HI Los Angeles Santa Monica Hostel is a vibrant and modern accommodation located just two blocks away from the beach. It offers a game room, complimentary Wi-Fi, and breakfast for guests. The hostel's prime location on LA's trendy West Side makes it an ideal choice for those looking to experience the California lifestyle. Guests can enjoy sunbathing in the courtyard, surfing at the nearby Pacific Ocean, or exploring popular attractions such as the Santa Monica Pier and Venice Beach.
name: HI Los Angeles Santa Monica Hostel
address: 1436 2nd St, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Once Will Rogers' ranch, this park features trails set in the canyon with views of LA & the ocean.
detail_description: Will Rogers State Historic Park, once the ranch of Will Rogers, a beloved American citizen and Hollywood actor, is a must-visit for nature enthusiasts in Los Angeles. The park offers various trails with stunning views of the city skyline and the ocean. Visitors can explore the 2-mile Inspiration Point loop trail or venture through the Santa Monica Mountains along the Rivas Canyon trail.
name: Will Rogers State Historic Park
address: 1501 Will Rogers State Park Rd, Pacific Palisades, CA 90272, USA

excerpt: City park featuring permanent chess tables & a human chessboard for players & spectators.
detail_description: Located just 500 feet south of the Santa Monica Pier, Chess Park is a must-visit for chess enthusiasts. The park features permanent chess tables and a human-sized chessboard where players and spectators can enjoy the game outdoors. Whether you're a serious player looking for a challenge or a family wanting to have some casual fun, this park has something for everyone. Visitors can watch intense games played by skilled individuals or join in on the action if they're up for it.
name: Chess Park
address: 1652 Ocean Front Walk, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Chic destination for elevated Italian cuisine in breezy, loungelike dining areas with ocean views.
detail_description: Ã‰lephante is a chic and elevated Italian restaurant located in Santa Monica, offering stunning ocean views and a breezy, loungelike atmosphere. The Sunset Room, with its natural stone and wood decor, provides the perfect setting for a romantic dining experience. The menu features coastal Italian cuisine with small plates like whipped aubergine and rigatoni verde with mushroom ragu, as well as signature desserts such as pavlova topped with white chocolate mousse.
name: Ã‰lephante
address: 1332 2nd St Rooftop, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Steaks, seafood & stiff drinks served in a nostalgic dining room known for celebrity sightings.
detail_description: Chez Jay is a legendary dining spot in Santa Monica that has been a favorite since 1959. This nautical-themed bar is famous for its celebrity sightings and offers a nostalgic experience. The restaurant serves delicious steaks, seafood, and strong drinks in a charmingly old-school atmosphere with peanut shells on the floor and a classic jukebox. It's been frequented by celebrities like the Rat Pack, Jim Morrison, and Marilyn Monroe due to its discreet location away from Hollywood.
name: Chez Jay
address: 1657 Ocean Ave, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Designed for children 8 & under, this museum boasts hands-on exhibits & frequent family programs.
detail_description: The Cayton Children's Museum, previously known as the Zimmer Children's Museum, is a vibrant space designed for children aged 8 and under. Located in Santa Monica, it offers 21,000 square feet of interactive exhibits and educational programs. The museum features hands-on activities such as a full-size helicopter, fire truck, veterinary clinic, and a climbing net that spans the entire space.
name: Cayton Children's Museum
address: 395 Santa Monica Pl Suite 374 Level 3, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Casual joint serving waffles in a range of breakfast & lunch dishes, including with fried chicken.
detail_description: Bru's Wiffle Santa Monica is a casual eatery that offers a diverse menu of waffle-based breakfast and lunch options, including the popular chicken and waffles. The restaurant is known for its unique and flavorful dishes, such as the Brus Toast with ice cream, fruit, and peanut butter, as well as the fiery Chicken on Fire featuring their secret sauce. With an extensive selection of waffles ranging from sweet to savory, there's something for every palate.
name: Bru's Wiffle Santa Monica
address: 2315 Wilshire Blvd, Santa Monica, CA 90403, USA

excerpt: This intimate comedy club & bar offers a variety of classes, open mikes & stand-up performances.
detail_description: Westside Comedy Theater is an intimate comedy club and bar in Santa Monica that has been a go-to spot for over a decade. It offers a variety of classes, open mics, and stand-up performances, providing a real stand-up experience with an authentic brick-wall backdrop. The venue has hosted notable comedians like Dave Chappelle, Adam Sandler, Dana Carvey, Judd Apatow, Tig Notaro, and many rising stars.
name: Westside Comedy Theater
address: 1323-A 3rd St, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

detail_description: Venice Boardwalk is a unique beach destination in Southern California, featuring a one-of-a-kind boardwalk right along the sand. The area is lined with shops offering an array of items from surfboards and wetsuits to hippie jewelry and incense. Visitors can also witness the famous Muscle Beach outdoor workout area and enjoy the sight of street performers, artists, and vendors creating a vibrant atmosphere.
name: Venice Boardwalk
address: Beach pavillion in, Los Angeles, CA, USA

excerpt: Independent movie theater with a throwback feel features vintage Hollywood & foreign films.
detail_description: The Aero Theatre, located at the corner of 14th Street and Montana Avenue, is a vintage movie theater with a nostalgic ambiance. Originally opened in 1940 by the Douglas Aircraft Company, it was later renovated by the nonprofit organization American Cinematheque. The single-screen theater underwent multiple renovations to enhance its facilities and now features new projection equipment and improved sound.
name: Aero Theatre
address: 1328 Montana Ave, Santa Monica, CA 90403, USA

detail_description: Rose Ave is a trendy and laid-back area located near the Venice border, offering a cool stretch of shops and dining options along Main Street. It's situated southeast of the region, providing a more relaxed atmosphere compared to the posh spots found northeast of downtown on Montana Avenue. This hip neighborhood is perfect for exploring unique eateries and stylish boutiques while enjoying a more low-key vibe.
name: Rose Ave
address: Los Angeles, CA, USA

detail_description: Camera Obscura, situated in Palisades Park in Santa Monica, is a distinctive attraction housed in a quirky mid-century modern building. It operates as a pinhole camera that captures outdoor images and projects them inside a dark room. This intriguing site has been around since 1898 and is currently located at the Senior Recreation Building after being moved several times over the years.
name: Camera Obscura
address: 1450 Ocean Park Blvd, Santa Monica, CA 90405, USA

name: Bergamot station
address: Olympic Blvd &, 26th St, Santa Monica, CA, USA

detail_description: Tips Toes Nail Studio is a beloved spot for nail care, known for its talented and friendly staff. Visitors appreciate the studio's clean and well-lit environment. Clients praise the efficient service and skilled execution of their desired nail styles, such as gel X nails with beautiful art. The studio's welcoming atmosphere and attention to detail keep customers coming back, making it a must-visit destination for top-notch nail treatments.
name: Tips Toes Nail Studio
address: 2106 Wilshire Blvd, Santa Monica, CA 90403, USA

detail_description: The Santa Monica Pier is a stunning destination that offers breathtaking views, especially during sunset. Picture yourself standing on the pier, feeling the gentle ocean breeze as you watch the sun dip below the horizon. It's a romantic spot where couples can share special moments while taking in the beauty of Los Angeles' coastline. The vibrant atmosphere and scenic backdrop make it an unforgettable experience for anyone visiting this iconic landmark.
name: Santa Monica pier
address: Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

detail_description: The Santa Monica Pier Carousel, a historic landmark at the beginning of the pier, boasts a classic 1922 carousel with 44 hand-carved animals including horses, a rabbit, and a goat. Originally from the Venice Pier, it was relocated to Santa Monica in 1947. The carousel operates under a classic Hippodrome and offers nostalgic fun for visitors. Despite some concerns about cleanliness and odor inside the attraction, many find it to be an enjoyable experience for both adults and children alike.
name: Santa Monica Pier Carousel
address: 1624 Ocean Front Walk, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

excerpt: Former tycoon's residence modeled after 1st-century Italian villa, with Greek & Roman artifacts.
detail_description: Nestled on a hill overlooking the Pacific Ocean, the Getty Villa is an architectural marvel inspired by a 1st-century Italian villa. This museum in Malibu, designed by Richard Meier, boasts classical architecture and serene gardens. It houses an impressive collection of Greek and Roman antiquities, including marble statues, mosaic floors, and Etruscan artwork. Visitors can explore replicas of ancient Roman architecture and admire artifacts such as frescoes from Pompeii and a bronze statue of an athlete.
name: The Getty Villa
address: 17985 Pacific Coast Hwy, Pacific Palisades, CA 90272, USA

excerpt: Regional history exhibits in the public library include rare photos, artifacts & rotating shows.
detail_description: The Santa Monica History Museum, housed in a charming 1914 Craftsman bungalow, offers a captivating journey through the local history of Santa Monica. The museum features regional history exhibits with rare photos, artifacts, and rotating shows that unveil the city's evolution from its Native American origins to its current status as a renowned tourist destination. Visitors can explore the 1800s and 1900s through AI images and immerse themselves in the world of bustling beach towns and elegant mansions.
name: Santa Monica History Museum
address: 1350 7th St, Santa Monica, CA 90401, USA

detail_description: The Lifeguard Tower 26 is an excellent location for beginners looking to learn how to surf within a 50-mile radius. The waves are shallow, ensuring that individuals can always stand up and never drift too far from where they can touch the ground. This beach offers a cool and serene atmosphere with very few people around. It provides occasional good waves without any undertow, making it a safe place to swim and enjoy a day at the beach. Moreover, there is ample street parking available for visitors.
name: Lifeguard Tower 26
address: 2600 Ocean Front Walk, Santa Monica, CA 90405, USA

excerpt: Busy beachfront park features paddle tennis, basketball & tennis courts, plus a grassy lawn & hill.
detail_description: Ocean View Park, located in Santa Monica, is a bustling beachfront park offering various recreational activities such as paddle tennis, basketball, and tennis courts. Visitors can bask in the laid-back atmosphere while enjoying stunning views of the Pacific Ocean from the grassy lawn or hill. The park also features a walking path connecting it to the beach, where beach volleyball and sunbathing are popular pastimes. Additionally, yoga and fitness classes are occasionally hosted by local instructors.
name: Ocean View Park
address: 2701 Barnard Way, Santa Monica, CA 90405, USA

excerpt: This beach-adjacent park features a playground, picnic areas & sculptures, plus restrooms.
detail_description: Dorothy Green Park, a 5-acre beachfront park situated on Barnard Way between Hart Avenue and Hill Street, offers a range of amenities for visitors to enjoy. This picturesque park features artistic displays, areas designated for picnicking, well-maintained footpaths suitable for walking, and convenient picnic tables. Additionally, there is a cafe available to cater to the needs of park-goers.
name: Dorothy Green Park
address: 2600 Barnard Way, Santa Monica, CA 90405, USA

detail_description: South Beach Park Playground is a fun and safe place for children to play during the summer. It features a climbing rope, swings, a roller slide, and a sandpit with water pump. The playground is located next to one of LAs best bike paths, making it perfect for adventurers of all ages.
name: South Beach Park Playground
address: 3400 Barnard Way, Santa Monica, CA 90405, USA
